/*
COPY ~Poisoned_pathways/spl/AC#PPWM.spl~         ~override~ // OLD wild magic spell effect in Myth Unnnohyr
LAF cd_new_portrait_icon INT_VAR string = RESOLVE_STR_REF(@903) STR_VAR bam_file = AC#WILMG RET icon END
COPY_EXISTING ~AC#PPWM.spl~         ~override~
LPF ALTER_EFFECT INT_VAR match_opcode = 142 match_parameter2 = 0 parameter2 = icon END
*/
COPY ~Poisoned_pathways/spl/AC#PPWI.spl~         ~override~ // NEW #2 wild magic spell effect in Myth Unnnohyr
LAF cd_new_portrait_icon INT_VAR string = RESOLVE_STR_REF(@903) STR_VAR bam_file = AC#WILMG RET icon END
COPY_EXISTING ~AC#PPWI.spl~         ~override~
LPF ALTER_EFFECT INT_VAR match_opcode = 142 match_parameter2 = 0 parameter2 = icon END

COPY ~Poisoned_pathways/spl/AC#PPDM.spl~         ~override~  // NEW dead magic area effect

//FINAL SPELL
/*
COPY ~Poisoned_pathways/spl/AC#PPXX.spl~ ~override~
  SAY NAME1 ~Brief Glimmer of Mythal~
  SAY NAME2 ~Brief Glimmer of Mythal~
  SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~BRIEF GLIMMER OF MYTHAL
This ability is a gift from Mythrien Serath himself. It allows the caster to call a brief gust of Mythal, powerful elven energy. when called, the caster gains +1 Luck and +6 Saving Throws vs. Spell and Saving Throws vs. Death for 1 turn. The spell cures poison and disease, as well as restores all lost levels. Furthermore, all allies in a close distance from the caster heal 4d4 Hit Points (6d4 if the ally is is an elf or half-elf) and removes all fatigue. Lastly, there is a 10% chance that allies will regain 1 first level spell (arcane and divine) while their fatigue is being removed.

This spell however, has a minor price, which should be taken into consideration. When the turn passes, the caster's visual range will be lowered by 4 and the fatigue that was removed from from the caster and the allies will be transfered to the caster.~
*/
COPY ~Poisoned_pathways/spl/AC#PPXXB.spl~ ~override~
  SAY NAME1 ~~
  SAY NAME2 ~~
  SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~~
  
COPY ~Poisoned_pathways/spl/AC#PPXXP.spl~ ~override~
  SAY NAME1 ~Blinded and tired~
  SAY NAME2 ~Blinded and tired~
  SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Blinded and tired~

